      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a good line. i want to lean into that tension a bit more for the subtext. \n\nwhen the younger cousin tries to defend themselves, how does the rest of the table usually react? like, do they all jump in to support the auntie, or is there a certain way they handle the conflict to keep things within the family? i'm trying to understand if there's a specific way these family dynamics or \"unspoken rules\" usually play out in these settings to make the script feel authentic.",
