      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The younger cousin might try to argue, but the rest of the table would likely react with a collective, almost subtle, shift in energy rather than an outright defense of the cousin. A few aunts might offer soft, noncommittal murmurs, looking down at their plates as if to say, \"Don't fight with her.\" The elders carry the weight of the conversation, and while some younger cousins might offer a quiet nod of agreement with the auntie, the overall dynamic is one of maintaining peace over winning the argument.",
